<p>Writing this scenario has two purposes. First, it lets us plan how our feature should behave.
And that's what we've been talking about. Second, we want the scenario to be executed as a test
to prove whether or not we have successfully created this behavior. To do that, we'll run
<code>./vendor/bin/behat</code> in our terminal and point it at <code>features/ls.feature</code> and let's see
what happens! </p>
<h2 id="the-essence-of-behat-matching-scenario-lines-with-functions">The Essence of Behat: Matching Scenario lines with Functions <a class="headerlink" href="using-behat#the-essence-of-behat-matching-scenario-lines-with-functions" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
