<p>So what does Behat really do? Simply, it reads each line of our scenario, looks for a matching
function inside of <code>FeatureContext</code> and calls it. In this case, it'll read
"There is a file named "john", find that it matches this annotation here
and then execute its function.</p>
<p>What's really cool is that because we surrounded john with quotes, it recognized that as a wildcard.
In the annotation, we have <code>:arg1</code> which means it matches anything surrounded in quotes or a number.</p>
<h2 id="filling-in-the-definitions-functions">Filling in the Definitions/Functions <a class="headerlink" href="using-behat#filling-in-the-definitions-functions" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
